Ecobank’s Nine-Month Profit Advances 55% as Loans Increase

-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 
2011-10-14T16:12:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/ecobank-s-nine-month-profit-advances-55-as-loans-increase-1-.html
Ecobank Transnational Inc. (ETI) ,  Africa ’s
largest lender by geographical spread, said profit jumped 55
percent in the nine months through September as loans and
deposits increased.  Net income increased to 19.1 billion naira ($119 million)
from 12.3 billion naira a year earlier, the company said in a
 statement  published on the website of the Nigerian Stock
Exchange today. Gross earnings for the period climbed to 124.4
billion naira from 93.6 billion naira, Ecobank said.  The Lome, Togo-based lender’s loans increased 17 percent to
1.17 trillion naira from 1 trillion naira a year earlier.
Deposits rose to 1.5 trillion naira from 1.25 trillion naira.  Ecobank’s shares declined 1 percent to 11.68 naira at the
close of trading in Lagos, Nigeria’s commercial capital. The
bank’s shares have slumped 26 percent this year compared with
the  Nigerian Stock Exchange  All-Share Index’s 20 percent
decline.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Kay in Abuja at 
